{{Infobox philosopher | region = Western Philosophy | era = [[Contemporary philosophy]] | image = | caption = | birth_date = 11 May 1968 | birth_place = [[Brčko]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]] | death_date = | death_place = | school_tradition = [[Continental philosophy]] | alma_mater = University of Sarajevo | notable_ideas = | main_interests = [[Pragmatism]], [[Neo-Marxism]], [[Ethics]], [[Ethnic nationalism]], [[Existentialism]] | influences = [[Richard Rorty]], [[W. E. B. Du Bois]], [[Frantz Fanon]], [[Martin Heidegger]], [[Edmund Husserl]], [[Jean-Paul Sartre]], [[Max Weber]], [[John Rawls]] }}
'''Asim Mujkić''' (born 11 May 1968) is a [[Bosnia]]n philosopher and sociologist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://novovrijeme.ba/intervju-prof-dr-asim-mujkic-probosanski-identitet-je-tesko-ugrozen/|title=Intervju prof. dr. Asim Mujkić: Probosanski identitet je teško ugrožen|publisher=Novovrijeme.ba}}</ref> Educated at the [[University of Sarajevo]], he works in the areas of ethics, phenomenology, philosophy of existence, philosophy of identity, social and political theory and theories on ethnicity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ba.n1info.com/a124089/Vijesti/Vijesti/Asim-Mujkic-Plasio-bih-se-da-sam-dio-politicke-elite-u-BiH.html|title=Asim Mujkić: Plašio bih se da sam dio političke elite u BiH|publisher=N1}}</ref> He has written particularly extensively on ethnicity and identity, ethnic phenomenology, existentialism, and on the works and thought of [[Richard Rorty]] and [[John Rawls]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oslobodjenje.ba/o2/kultura/knjizevnost/asim-mujkic-ravnopravno-doprinosimo-u-raspravi-oko-vaznih-politickih-problema|title=Asim Mujkić: Ravnopravno doprinosimo u raspravi oko važnih političkih problema|publisher=Oslobođenje}}</ref> He is a professor at the University of Sarajevo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://depo.ba/clanak/152861/asim-mujkic-sda-nema-sta-slaviti-a-sto-se-tice-tzv-ljevice-koja-se-otima-za-bosnjacke-glasove-mogu-reci-da|title=Asim Mujkić: SDA nema šta slaviti, a što se tiče tzv. ljevice koja se otima za bošnjačke glasove, mogu reći da...|publisher=Depo.ba}}</ref>
==Biography==
He studied philosophy and sociology at the University of Sarajevo where he graduated in 1991. He earned his post-graduate degree from the same institution in 1998 with a thesis on the neopragmatism of Richard Rorty. In 2002 he earned his PhD with a thesis on the antiessentialist character of the philosophy of pragmatism. He was named Centennial Professor and head of the departament of philosophy at the [[Faculty of Political Science in Sarajevo]], lecturing on the subjects of introductory philosophy, ethics and political ethics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fpn.unsa.ba/bs/wp-content/uploads/syll/LJS-2015-16/K/BA-UVOD-U-FILOZOFIJU.pdf|title=Odsjek za filozofiju, sociologiju i politologiju|publisher=University of Sarajevo}}</ref> He is the chairman of the Association of Bosnian political scientists, as well as the deputy editor-in-chief of the [[Odjek]] journal for the arts and humanities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.odjek.ba/index.php?broj=14&id=15|title=UČO I EIRONIK|publisher=Odjek.ba}}</ref> He is one of the founders of the [[Open University of Sarajevo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiosarajevo.ba/metromahala/teme/uskoro-pocinje-sesti-otvoreni-univerzitet-sarajevo-pod-nazviom-sta-da-se-radi/280285|title=Uskoro počinje šesti Otvoreni univerzitet Sarajevo pod nazviom "Šta da se radi?"|publisher=Radio Sarajevo}}</ref>
