{{Infobox academic |name =Howard Augustine Ozmon, Jr. |image =Howard A. Ozmon headshot.jpg |caption = |birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1929|12|11}} |birth_place = [[Portsmouth, Virginia]] |death_date =September 6, 2014 |death_place =Hollywood, Florida |school_tradition = Eastern and Western Philosophy |main_interests = [[Philosophy of Education]], [[Social Justice]] }}
'''Howard Augustine Ozmon, Jr.''' (born 1929) was a retired professor emeritus of [[Virginia Commonwealth University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soe.vcu.edu/faculty/emeritus.html/ |title=VCU School of Education, Faculty and Staff |accessdate=2010-10-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100609083329/http://www.soe.vcu.edu/faculty/emeritus.html |archivedate=June 9, 2010 }}</ref>
He lived in [[Portsmouth, Virginia]], and received an A.A. degree from St. Bernard College in [[Alabama]], a B.A. from the [[University of Virginia]] Alumni 1954 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://uvamagazine.org/classnotes/1954|title=The University of Virginia Magazine Classnotes|accessdate=2010-10-26}}</ref> in Philosophy, a Master of Arts in International and Comparative Education, and an Ed.D. in Philosophy of Education from Teachers College, [[Columbia University]]. He taught in the public schools of New York and New Jersey, and at several colleges and universities, including the University of Virginia and Virginia Commonwealth University.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soe.vcu.edu|title=School of Education of The University of Virginia|accessdate=2010-10-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.community.vcu.edu/programs/retiredfaculty/index.html |title=School of Education of Virginia Commonwealth Education, Retired Faculty |accessdate=2010-10-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100609013452/http://www.community.vcu.edu/programs/retiredfaculty/index.html |archivedate=June 9, 2010 }}</ref> He was also professor and chairman of the Department of Education at [[Chicago State University]].
Dr. Ozmon is the author of many books and articles dealing with philosophy and education, including the eighth edition of ''Philosophical Foundations of Education'' re-published by Merrill Prentice-Hall (2008 & 2012). He is also a writer of novels, short stories, plays, and books for children including the following:
*Challenging Ideas in Education *Dialogue in the Philosophy of Education (The Coordinated Teacher Preparation Series) *Utopias and Education, Tall Enterprises, 1980 *Twelve Great Philosophers (The Wonderful World of Children's Books) *Contemporary Critics of Education *Challenging Ideas in Education
Howard lived in [[Hollywood, Florida]]at the time of his death.
