The '''Lion Throne''' is the [[English language|English]] term used to identify the [[throne]] of the [[Dalai Lama]] of [[Tibet]]. It specifically refers to the throne historically used by Dalai Lamas at [[Potala Palace]] in [[Lhasa]].<ref>{{Citation|first=John M.|last=Burns|title=Dalai Lama Finds China's Threats A Subject for Humor and Anxiety|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/03/06/world/dalai-lama-finds-china-s-threats-a-subject-for-humor-and-anxiety.html?pagewanted=4|date=March 6, 1996|accessdate=February 22, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Dalai Lama concludes Japan tour|publisher=[[Phayul]]|url=http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?article=Dalai+Lama+concludes+Japan+tour&id=25909|date=November 7, 2009|accessdate=February 22, 2011}}</ref>
