{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}
'''Otto Pöggeler''' (12 December 1928 in [[Attendorn]] – 10 December 2014) was a [[Germany|German]] [[philosopher]]. He specialized in [[Phenomenology (philosophy)|phenomenology]] and commenting on [[Heidegger]].<ref>[http://www.discogs.com/artist/Otto+Pöggeler Otto Pöggeler Discography at Discogs]</ref> In 1963 he authored the acclaimed ''Martin Heidegger’s Path of Thinking'', one of the first rigorous attempts at tracing the development of Heidegger’s thought. He also published a study of poetry of [[Paul Celan]], and was director of the [[Hegel Archive]] at the [[Ruhr University]] in Bochum.<ref name="Wolin1993">{{cite book|last=Pöggeler|first=Otto|title=The Heidegger Controversy: A Critical Reader|editor-last=Wolin|editor-first=Richard|editor-link=Richard Wolin|chapter=Heidegger's political self-understanding|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ur53pdJAdpUC&pg=PA198|publisher=[[MIT Press]]|year=1993|page=198|accessdate=21 September 2013|isbn=978-0-262-73101-0}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://lebenswege.faz.net/40124767-death-otto-poggeler|title=Otto Pöggeler Traueranzeige|publisher=lebenswege.faz.net|date=13 December 2014|language=German|work=Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung}}</ref>

